A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the lives and legacy of Kelly Nelon Clark, Jason Clark, and Amber Nelon Kistler
2 of The Nelons and commending Autumn Nelon Streetman; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, The Nelons, a renowned Southern Gospel group originating from Georgia, have
4 captivated audiences since their founding in 1977 by Rex Nelon as The Rex Nelon Singers,
5 later becoming known simply as The Nelons; and
6 WHEREAS, over their decades-long career, The Nelons have released more than 35 albums,
7 achieved more than 20 Top 5 Southern Gospel radio singles, and inspired countless listeners
8 through their harmonious blend of Gospel, a capella, hymns, Americana, folk, and
9 inspirational music; and
10 WHEREAS, their contributions to Gospel music were formally recognized upon their
11 induction into the Gospel Music Association Hall of Fame in 2016, cementing their legacy
12 as one of the genre's most influential groups; and
13 WHEREAS, on July 26, 2024, the Gospel music community suffered an immeasurable loss
14 when three beloved members of The Nelons—Kelly Nelon Clark; her husband, Jason Clark;
