15 and their daughter, Amber Nelon Kistler—tragically lost their lives in a plane crash while
16 traveling to perform on the Gaither Homecoming Cruise to Alaska; and
17 WHEREAS, Autumn Nelon Streetman, the surviving member of the family group, has
18 demonstrated extraordinary resilience in the face of this profound loss, carrying forward her
19 family's musical heritage with strength and dedication; and
20 WHEREAS, in August 2024, she released the album Loving You, which was completed
21 shortly before the tragedy and was later nominated for Best Roots Gospel Album at the 2025
22 Grammy Awards; and
23 WHEREAS, Autumn Nelon Streetman remains committed to honoring her family's legacy
24 and ensuring that The Nelons' message of faith, hope, and love continues to uplift audiences
25 for generations to come.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body honor the lives and legacy of Kelly Nelon Clark, Jason Clark, and
28 Amber Nelon Kistler of The Nelons; commend Autumn Nelon Streetman for her immense
29 resilience and strength; and extend the deepest and most sincere condolences.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Autumn Nelon Streetman.
